events.name: Introduction to User Experience Design
events.description:
User Experience! Do you know guys about UX design and What it means?

You might have heard that UX is one of the fastest growing and highest paying professions around, best work-life balance and you get to be creative! So what is user experience (UX) design? Why is it so big right now? And How UX design can enhance people’s lives?

Currently, a huge number of people are turning into UX and try to invest in it with almost no experience what the UX industry is like! And that is why we are here!

The good news is, there’s never been a better time to learn about user experience (UX). Whether you are interested in this field, or you just want to learn the principles of UX to create better products, and design better experiences, we’re here to help you get started.

A session about UX will take place next Thursday, March 14th, 2019 as a part of the Scientific Day of the Hijjawi Faculty for Engineering Technology at Yarmouk University. We’ll share what UX is with you.

events.name: Machine Learning Study Jam

venue.name: SDK Training Center
venue.address_1: Al-Naseem Traffic Lights - Al-Hmaydeh Complex the 3rd Floor.

events.description:
Hello Friends!

We’re super excited to bring Google's latest Machine Learning offering - ‘Machine Learning Crash Course (MLCC)’ to Jordan. This course is intended for those who wish to learn about ML from a practical, applied perspective that will enable them to use machine learning within their everyday projects, and who wish to benefit from the power of TensorFlow wrapped in convenient higher-level abstractions. This is a great opportunity for professionals, entrepreneurs, and students to gain some practical experience in ML and TensorFlow.

This course will be suitable for you, if:
- You are a strong programmer
- Ideally, you are at least somewhat familiar with Python. You don't need to be an expert.
- Ideally, you know at least a little about linear algebra and calculus.

This course is not recommended for:
- Participants with extensive machine learning backgrounds.
- Participants looking to learn about the lower-level intricacies of raw TensorFlow.
Although the course does contain some basic TensorFlow exercises, most of the exercises focus on high-level Tensor APIs.
Participants seeking advanced topics in machine learning such as image conventional models and recurrent/sequential models.

The format of this course:
We will be walking you through MLCC, its modules, and basic ML concepts. Additionally, we will have you go through selected modules of the course, with a teaching assistant guiding you in course’s practical pieces/exercises and troubleshooting and pieces of the content where you are struggling. The course is open to all so you can complete the remaining modules as a self-study after the session.

Other requirements? Additionally, we’d need you to bring:
- Your laptop and charger. You will need this to go through the online course.
- Pen & paper (or any other preferable option if you plan to take notes)
A can-do attitude!

Interested?
- Register here: https://forms.gle/ipBCdWPGeeztjoVs9 by 20 April.

Selected attendees would be notified by 25 April. Filling up this form doesn’t guarantee a confirmation.

Thanks!
